4 SJR___ COMMENDING LIEUTENANT GOVERNOR WILL AINSWORTH FOR HIS
5 SERVICE TO THE STATE OF ALABAMA.
6
7 WHEREAS, with utmost admiration and sincere respect,
8 we take great pride in commending Alabama's 31st Lieutenant
9 Governor William "Will" Ainsworth for his many
10 accomplishments toward the betterment of our state,
11 especially in the areas of workforce development, military
12 support, and tax reform; and
13 WHEREAS, Will Ainsworth was born in Birmingham to
14 Billy and Sharon Ainsworth in 1981; he grew up in Boaz and
15 graduated from Westbrook Christian School in 1999; after
16 attaining a Bachelor's degree in marketing from Auburn
17 University in 2004, he returned to Marshall County and
18 served Albertville's Grace Fellowship Church as a youth
19 pastor; and
20 WHEREAS, along with his brother, Austin, Lt. Governor
21 Ainsworth opened Dream Ranch Hunting Lodge in Guntersville
22 in 2003; he also founded the Tennessee Valley Hunting and
23 Fishing Expo in 2011 and became a real estate investor
24 specializing in residential construction and development; in
25 addition, he operates a commercial cattle operation in
26 Guntersville; and
27 WHEREAS, after answering the call to serve his
28 community through elected office, Lt. Governor Ainsworth won
Page 1

community through elected office, Lt. Governor Ainsworth won
SJR105 INTRODUCED
29 a 27th District Seat in the Alabama House of Representatives
30 in 2014; while serving in the House, he was a champion for
31 pre-K, K-12, and higher education; passed election integrity
32 legislation; and emphasized issues relating to business,
33 agriculture, and family values; and
34 WHEREAS, keeping a self-imposed legislative term
35 limit promise, Lt. Governor Ainsworth declared his candidacy
36 for lieutenant governor in 2018 and received the most votes
37 of any candidate for constitutional office on the general
38 election ballot; he was elected to a second term without
39 major party opposition in 2022; and
40 WHEREAS, during the 2023 Legislative Session, Lt.
41 Governor Ainsworth was the chief architect and proponent of
42 the largest tax cut in Alabama history, a $300 million
43 reduction in the state sales tax on groceries; he has also
44 been instrumental in renewing the Alabama Jobs Act and
45 Growing Alabama, to ensure that our state remains
46 competitive in recruiting high-paying 21st century jobs; and
47 WHEREAS, as Chair of the Alabama Small Business
48 Commission, Lt. Governor Ainsworth has worked to promote
49 policies that grow and expand both new and existing
50 businesses, from small, mom-and-pop operations to Alabama's
51 largest employers; and
52 WHEREAS, under his leadership, the Alabama Military
53 Stability Commission has passed dozens of bills in the
54 Legislature to ensure Alabama remains the nation's most
55 welcoming state to active soldiers and veterans; in 2024, he
56 highlighted the enactment of a 10-bill pro-military package
Page 2

highlighted the enactment of a 10-bill pro-military package
SJR105 INTRODUCED
57 and launched the Heroes Welcome website as a resource for
58 transitioning families; as a result, his efforts on behalf
59 of military members and their families earned Lt. Governor
60 Ainsworth the Pete Taylor Award from the U.S. Department of
61 Defense; and
62 WHEREAS, he also served as National Chair of the
63 Aerospace States Association, a group of elected officials,
64 academics, and private sector entities from states with ties
65 to the aviation and spaceflight industries; Lt. Governor
66 Ainsworth has served as a strong advocate for Alabama's
67 aerospace industry, promoted STEM education in K-12 schools,
68 and has pushed the Pentagon to maintain its commitment of
69 placing U.S. Space Command Headquarters in Huntsville; he
70 also launched an aerospace internship program, as well as an
71 aerospace supplier program; and
72 WHEREAS, perhaps one of Lt. Governor Ainsworth's more
73 visible accomplishments to visitors touring our state is his
74 "Go Wide I-65" campaign to widen the interstate to at least
75 three lanes on each side from the Tennessee state line down
76 to Alabama's Gulf Coast, aiding safety, traffic congestion,
77 and statewide economic impact; and
78 WHEREAS, Lt. Governor Ainsworth is married to the
79 former Kendall Foster, and they are the proud parents of
80 Hunter, Hays, and Addie; the Ainsworths are members of
81 Gilliam Springs Baptist Church in Arab, where Kendall
82 teaches the Children's Sunday School Class; Lt. Governor
83 Ainsworth enjoys spending time with his family in the
84 outdoors, coaching, and playing sports; and
